id§NOT_1507823362607°datum§12.10.2017°DatumE§2017-10-12-00-00-00_NOT_1507823362607°art§Wissen°name§Apache / Webserver / Browser Caching°info§<p>Apache Caching Guide:&nbsp;<a href="https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/caching.html">https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/caching.html</a>&nbsp; </p><p>mod_cache: <a href="https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_cache.html">https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_cache.html</a><a href="https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_cache.html"></a></p><p>mod_cache_disk:&nbsp;<a href="https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_cache_disk.html" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_cache_disk.html</a></p><p>mod_cache_socache:&nbsp;<a href="https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_cache_socache.html">https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_cache_socache.html</a></p><p><a href="https://www.mnot.net/cache_docs/" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">https://www.mnot.net/cache_docs/</a><br></p><p><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9884513/avoid-caching-of-the-http-responses">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9884513/avoid-caching-of-the-http-responses</a><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9884513/avoid-caching-of-the-http-responses"></a></p><p>Intro/Guide:&nbsp;<a href="https://varvy.com/pagespeed/cache-control.html">https://varvy.com/pagespeed/cache-control.html</a></p><p><a href="http://www.serverlab.ca/tutorials/linux/web-servers-linux/improve-website-performance-by-enabling-caching-in-apache/">http://www.serverlab.ca/tutorials/linux/web-servers-linux/improve-website-performance-by-enabling-caching-in-apache/</a></p>°text§<p>Apache Caching Guide:&nbsp;<a href="https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/caching.html">https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/caching.html</a>&nbsp; </p><p>mod_cache: <a href="https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_cache.html">https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_cache.html</a><a href="https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_cache.html"></a></p><p>mod_cache_disk:&nbsp;<a href="https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_cache_disk.html" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_cache_disk.html</a></p><p>mod_cache_socache:&nbsp;<a href="https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_cache_socache.html">https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_cache_socache.html</a></p><p><a href="https://www.mnot.net/cache_docs/" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">https://www.mnot.net/cache_docs/</a><br></p><p><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9884513/avoid-caching-of-the-http-responses">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9884513/avoid-caching-of-the-http-responses</a><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9884513/avoid-caching-of-the-http-responses"></a></p><p>Intro/Guide:&nbsp;<a href="https://varvy.com/pagespeed/cache-control.html">https://varvy.com/pagespeed/cache-control.html</a></p><p><a href="http://www.serverlab.ca/tutorials/linux/web-servers-linux/improve-website-performance-by-enabling-caching-in-apache/">http://www.serverlab.ca/tutorials/linux/web-servers-linux/improve-website-performance-by-enabling-caching-in-apache/</a></p><br/>-----<br/><p>Wenn die DocRoot auf einem mounted FS liegt (Bsp Vagrant RHEL-Box) ist es evtl. notwendig, in httpd.conf und/oder VHOST einzustellen:</p><p><b>EnableSendfile Off</b></p><p><a href="https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/de/mod/core.html#enablesendfile">https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/de/mod/core.html#enablesendfile</a></p><p><br></p><p>Caching Kontrolle im Browser und Apache - beachte diese Response Headers / Request Headers:</p><p>Cache-Control, Expires, Last-Modified, Etag,&nbsp;Pragma</p><p>&lt;IfModule mod_expires.c&gt;</p><p>&nbsp; <b>ExpiresActive</b> On</p><p>&nbsp; <b>ExpiresDefault</b> "access plus 0 minutes"</p><p>&nbsp; <b>ExpiresByType</b> text/css "access plus 2 seconds"&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp; ExpiresByType text/html "access plus 2 seconds"&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&lt;/IfModule&gt;</p><p><br></p><p>&lt;IfModule mod_headers.c&gt;</p><p>&nbsp; #&nbsp;<b>FileEtag</b> MTime Size</p><p>&nbsp; # Header unset <b>ETag</b></p><p>&nbsp; # Browser das Caching verbieten</p><p>&nbsp; Header set <b>Cache-Control</b> "private, max-age=0, no-store"</p><p># Header set Cache-Control "private, max-age=0, no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, proxy-revalidate"</p><p>&nbsp; Header set <b>Pragma</b> no-cache</p><p>&lt;/IfModule&gt;</p><p><br></p>°files§